Reelection Machine,&quot; in Eric Felten, <i>The Ruling Class</i> (Washington, D.C.: Regnery Gateway, 1993), 
p. 183.
<P>
<P><TT><B><A NAME="4">4</A></B></TT> Bundling is the practice of gathering checks from many individuals in an organization and delivering them as a package to a campaign in order to draw attention to the group. Soft money is a donation to a political party for use in general partybuilding efforts such as voter registration and get-out-the-vote campaigns.
<P>
<P><TT><B><A NAME="5">5</A></B></TT> Federal Election Commission reports 
state that Fulani received $938,798.45 in public 
